; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures timer2 and generates a oneshot interrupt.
;
; B. Preparation
;    N/A
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. Timer2
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. Timer20 : PB3 (Output)
;               : PB10 (Capture Input)
;               : PA5 (External Clock Input)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; Timer20
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (Timer20)
;
; 2. Clock                     : [ 0 m h 10 1000]
;    Source                    : m ( MCCR : Misc Clock )
;    MCCR Source               : h ( HSI : High Speed Internal Clock - 48MHz )
;    Source Divide             : 10 
;    Timer2 Pre-Divide         : 1000 ( MCCR Clock / 10 ) / 1000
;
; 3. Config                    : [ 0 i o h 4800 4800 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : o (One-Shot) 
;    Output Port Polarity      : h (High)
;    A Data                    : 4800
;    B Data                    : 4800
;
; Timer20
sendln 'cm timer2'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 0 m h 10 1000'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i o h 4800 4800'
mpause 30
sendln 'log on'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
